# git-secrets allowlist for Daisy.
#
# Each line is a regex pattern. Anything matching one of these
# patterns is NOT flagged by `git secrets --scan` even if it
# matches a registered prohibited pattern.
#
# Rule of thumb: only ever allow values that are PUBLIC by design.
# Real secrets stay in macOS Keychain via KeychainStore; user-
# supplied API keys (Anthropic, OpenAI, MCP, Google access tokens)
# never touch the repo.

# Google OAuth client_secret used in the PKCE + loopback redirect
# flow (GoogleOAuthClient.swift).
#
# Why this is safe: Google's "Desktop app" OAuth client type ships
# its client_secret in the binary by design — anyone with a stock
# Chrome / VS Code / Daisy install can extract it from disk in
# seconds. Security comes from PKCE + the redirect_uri being a
# loopback http://127.0.0.1:<random-port> path that only Daisy
# itself can serve. Documented at length inside GoogleOAuthClient.swift
# and the memory entry project_daisy_google_oauth.md.
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
